article.description: — JaKobe Coles had 14 points off the bench to lead Butler to a 70-64 win over Providence on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Coles scores 14 to carry Butler past Providence 70-64
article.linkText: Coles scores 14 to carry Butler past Providence 70-64
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- — JaKobe Coles had 14 points off the bench to lead Butler to a 70-64 win over Providence on Wednesday night. Bryce Golden had 11 points for Butler (2-3, 1-1 Big East Conference). Jair Bolden added 11 points and Bryce Nze had 10 points. Nate Watson had 19 points for the Friars (5-3, 1-1). David Duke added 17 points and eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
